# Content Strategy and Maintenance Guidelines

## Content Strategy Overview

The WINET Lab website serves as the primary digital presence for the laboratory, providing comprehensive information about research, team members, seminars, and laboratory activities. Content management follows a structured approach to ensure consistency, accuracy, and engagement.

### Primary Content Categories

#### Research and Academic Content
- **Research Areas**: Detailed descriptions of laboratory focus areas from [data/research.json](mdc:data/research.json)
- **Publications**: Academic papers, conference proceedings, and research outputs
- **Project Documentation**: Ongoing and completed research projects
- **Collaboration Information**: Partner institutions and joint research initiatives

#### Team and Personnel Content
- **Faculty Profiles**: Comprehensive profiles following [team-data-management.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/team-data-management.mdc) guidelines
- **Student Information**: PhD, postdoc, and visiting scholar profiles
- **Alumni Network**: Former members with achievement tracking
- **Recruitment Materials**: Open positions and application information

#### Events and Seminars
- **Seminar Series**: Following [seminar-management.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/seminar-management.mdc) standards
- **Workshop Documentation**: Specialized events and training sessions
- **Conference Participation**: Laboratory presence at academic conferences
- **Industry Engagement**: Corporate partnerships and technology transfer activities

#### News and Updates
- **Laboratory News**: Achievements, awards, and milestones
- **Student Achievements**: Graduations, publications, and recognitions
- **Funding Announcements**: Grant awards and research funding
- **Media Coverage**: Press releases and external coverage

## Content Creation Workflows

### New Content Development

#### Research Area Updates
1. **Content Planning**
   - Identify new research directions and funding areas
   - Collaborate with faculty to define scope and impact
   - Align with laboratory strategic priorities
   - Review competitive landscape and positioning

2. **Content Creation**
   - Draft comprehensive descriptions with technical depth
   - Include practical applications and societal impact
   - Incorporate relevant keywords for discoverability
   - Add supporting visuals and diagrams when helpful

3. **Review and Approval**
   - Technical review by relevant faculty members
   - Editorial review for clarity and accessibility
   - Legal review for intellectual property considerations
   - Final approval by laboratory leadership

#### Team Member Content
1. **Information Gathering**
   - Collect standardized information using established templates
   - Obtain high-quality professional photographs
   - Verify institutional affiliations and contact information
   - Gather research interests and publication highlights

2. **Profile Development**
   - Follow YAML schema requirements from [team-data-management.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/team-data-management.mdc)
   - Write engaging biographies that highlight expertise
   - Include collaboration opportunities and contact methods
   - Ensure consistency with laboratory branding and tone

3. **Integration and Testing**
   - Add profiles to appropriate directory structure
   - Test dynamic loading and display functionality
   - Verify all links and contact information
   - Ensure mobile responsiveness and accessibility

### Content Updates and Maintenance

#### Regular Review Schedule
- **Weekly**: News items, seminar announcements, and urgent updates
- **Monthly**: Team member information, publication lists, and project status
- **Quarterly**: Research area descriptions, strategic priorities, and partnerships
- **Annually**: Complete content audit, archive management, and strategy review

#### Update Prioritization
1. **Critical Updates**: Security issues, contact information, emergency announcements
2. **High Priority**: New team members, major research announcements, funding news
3. **Medium Priority**: Publication updates, seminar materials, project documentation
4. **Low Priority**: Minor text improvements, image optimization, archival organization

## Editorial Standards and Guidelines

### Writing Style and Tone
- **Academic Professional**: Maintain scholarly credibility while ensuring accessibility
- **Inclusive Language**: Use gender-neutral and culturally sensitive terminology
- **Active Voice**: Prefer active voice for clarity and engagement
- **Conciseness**: Balance comprehensive information with readability
- **Technical Accuracy**: Ensure all technical content is precise and current

### Content Structure Standards
```markdown
# Page/Section Title (H1)
[Brief introduction paragraph establishing context and purpose]

## Main Section (H2)
[Substantive content with clear organization]

### Subsection (H3)
[Detailed information with supporting evidence]

#### Specific Topics (H4)
[Granular details and technical specifications]
```

### Language and Terminology
- **Consistency**: Use standardized terminology throughout the website
- **Accessibility**: Define technical terms and acronyms on first use
- **International Audience**: Consider non-native English speakers in word choice
- **SEO Optimization**: Include relevant keywords naturally in content
- **Institutional Voice**: Maintain consistency with university communication standards

## SEO and Content Optimization

### Search Engine Optimization Strategy
- **Keyword Research**: Identify relevant academic and technical keywords
- **Content Optimization**: Natural keyword integration without stuffing
- **Meta Information**: Comprehensive title tags and descriptions
- **Internal Linking**: Strategic cross-references between related content
- **External Authority**: Link to reputable academic and institutional sources

### Technical SEO Implementation
```html
<!-- Page-specific meta tags -->
<meta name="description" content="Specific, compelling description under 160 characters">
<meta name="keywords" content="research, wireless networking, smart cities, IoT">
<meta name="author" content="WINET Lab, City University of Hong Kong">

<!-- Open Graph for social sharing -->
<meta property="og:title" content="Page Title | JC STEM Lab of Smart City">
<meta property="og:description" content="Page description for social media">
<meta property="og:image" content="https://domain.com/image.jpg">
<meta property="og:url" content="https://domain.com/page-url">

<!-- Academic meta tags -->
<meta name="citation_title" content="Research Paper Title">
<meta name="citation_author" content="Author Name">
<meta name="citation_publication_date" content="2024/01/15">
```

